\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. A. bourgaei} Boiss. ex Milde,{\i  Bot. Zeit. }{\b 24:} 384 (1866). Rhizome caespitose. Leaves 4-28 cm; petiole up to 1/3 as long as the lamina, green above, blackish below; lamina linear-lanceolate, 1-pinnate; pinnae 8-20 opposite pairs, the acroscopic base adnate, forming a wing on the rhachis, pinnatifid, the segments crenulate towards the apex. 2n = 72.{\i  Shady crevices of limestone rocks. Karpathos.} Cr. ({\i E. Mediterranean region.})
