\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. A. obovatum} Viv., {\i Fl. Lib.} 68 (1824). Rhizome-scales narrow, becoming filiform at the apex of the rhizome. Leaves 15-30 cm; petiole up to as long as the lamina, but not less than ½ its length, not swollen below, light reddish-brown, with few filiform scales; lamina ovate-lanceolate, acuminate, bright green, glabrous, 2-pinnate, the rhachis and midrib with occasional filiform scales; pinnae 2-4 cm, ovate-triangular, pinnately divided only in proximal ½, pinnatifid distally; pinnules suborbicular, with obtuse, mucronate teeth. Sori ovate, nearer margin than midrib. {\i Ledges, rocks and walls, often near the sea. • W. Europe and Mediterranean region}. Az Be Br Co Cr Ga Gr Hb He Hs He It ?Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
